title.narrative: By 2020, communities in target rural and peri-urban areas, small towns, schools and health centres, achieve open defecation freestatus, with increased access to adequate sanitation services, improved hygiene practices.

description.narrative: UNICEF continued providing support for scaling-up sanitation at community and institutional levels. A total of 2,576 communities were declared ODF, of which 93 per cent (2,395) were directly attributed to UNICEF and the remaining communities through substantive UNICEF support at upstream and downstream levels. UNICEF ensured access to basic sanitation for836,326 people and 95 schools gained access to sanitation facilities benefiting 91,370 learners. WASH infrastructure construction works were completed in 33 health centres by end 2021, construction was in progress in 15 health centres, and an additional 85 health centres were in the planning (35) and design (50) stages. | Status:Met | As-of Date:11/01/2022
